content:
{
  "plan": "Round 1, start of initiative. No surprise round is indicated in the encounter setup or prior narration—both sides are aware and prepared for combat at the outset. Initiative order is: Corrupted Wolf_2 (11), Corrupted Wolf (10), Scout Kira (10), Eirik Hearthwise (6), Corrupted Wolf_3 (1). Proceeding to Corrupted Wolf_2's turn. DO NOT prompt player yet. Monster turn still active.",
  "narration": "You tense, recalling the hope of catching these beasts unaware. But as your hands move toward your crossbow, the corrupted wolves snap their heads in your direction—their senses already fixed on you, alert and ready to strike. Whatever force twisted them has made them too wary, too hungry to let you launch the first attack uncontested. These predators refuse to be ambushed.\n\nKira glances at you with a grim shake of her head. 'No advantage this time. They're ready.' Her voice is taut, her bowstring drawn, but the initiative now belongs to the unnatural wolves.\n\nWith a snarl, the nearest wolf lunges forward, hackles raised and blackened teeth bared. The battle for the clearing begins in earnest.",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 1, start of wolf turn. Initiative order: Corrupted Wolf_2 (11), Corrupted Wolf (10), Scout Kira (10), Eirik Hearthwise (6), Corrupted Wolf_3 (1). First up: Corrupted Wolf_2. It will lunge at the closest visible target—likely Kira as the more lightly armored and ranged threat. Corrupted Wolf_2 uses its first attack (Bite, CREATURE ATTACKS d20 [2]+4=6 vs AC 15). This will miss. Corrupted Wolf_2's second attack (Corrupting Bite, CREATURE ATTACKS d20 [12]+4=16 vs AC 15) will hit. Corrupting Bite deals 1d6+2 necrotic damage (GENERIC DICE d6 [5]+2=7 necrotic). After this, Corrupted Wolf (initiative 10) acts next, targeting Eirik with a Bite (CREATURE ATTACKS d20 [7]+4=11 vs AC 17, miss) and then a Corrupting Bite (CREATURE ATTACKS d20 [14]+4=18 vs AC 17, hit). Damage: 1d6+2 necrotic (GENERIC DICE d6 [2]+2=4 necrotic). After both wolves, Kira (initiative 10) will take her turn. Player does not act yet.",
  "narration": "The corrupted wolves surge into motion, snapping out of the fog with terrifying speed. The second wolf, its jaws dripping with black rot, barrels past the wagon and hurls itself at Kira. Its first bite glances off her darting form, but the second sinks into her arm, and you see her grimace as the wound pulses with sickly, unnatural energy. Dark veins momentarily crawl up her skin as the necrotic bite takes hold.\n\nAt the same moment, the largest wolf wheels toward you. Its initial snap at your shield is wild, but before you can recover, it twists and tears into your thigh with a foul, corrupting bite. A chill spreads from the wound—not just pain, but something darker gnawing into your flesh.\n\nKira staggers, then grits her teeth and shakes the corruption from her mind. She lifts her bow, already seeking a vulnerable spot on the nearest wolf. The beasts' eyes gleam with inhuman hunger, and the fight has already drawn blood.",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "scout_kira",
        "changes": "Takes 7 necrotic damage from Corrupted Wolf_2's corrupting bite. Kira is now at 3 out of 10 HP."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "Takes 4 necrotic damage from Corrupted Wolf's corrupting bite. Eirik is now at 7 out of 11 HP."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 1, Scout Kira's turn. Initiative order so far: Corrupted Wolf_2 (attacked, dealt 7 necrotic to Kira), Corrupted Wolf (attacked, dealt 4 necrotic to Eirik), next is Scout Kira (10). After Kira it will be Eirik Hearthwise (player, 6), then Corrupted Wolf_3 (1). Player turn is NOT active yet. DO NOT prompt Eirik for action yet. Kira will attack the most dangerous wolf—likely the one that bit her (Corrupted Wolf_2)—using her shortbow (CREATURE ATTACKS d20 [12]+4=16 vs AC 13, HIT). Sneak Attack applies (Eirik is within 5 feet of Corrupted Wolf_2 as an ally). Damage: 1d6+3 (shortbow) [GENERIC DICE d6 [3]+3=6], plus 1d6 Sneak Attack [GENERIC DICE d6 [2]]=2. Total: 8 piercing damage. After Kira, it will be Eirik's turn.",
  "narration": "Scout Kira, blood soaking her sleeve from the wolf's corrupting bite, draws in a shaky breath. With practiced speed, she nocks an arrow and lets fly at the beast that wounded her. The arrow whistles through the air and buries itself deep in the wolf's shoulder. The corrupted creature yelps, black ichor spurting from the wound as it staggers back, momentarily thrown off-balance.\n\nKira grits her teeth and gives you a tense, hopeful glance. 'I’ll keep it distracted, Eirik—hit it hard!'\n\nThe wolf is wounded, but her injuries look serious. The wolves’ eyes glow hungrily as they refocus on you. The tide could turn in an instant.",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "TW01-E2",
        "changes": "Corrupted Wolf_2 takes 8 piercing damage from Scout Kira's shortbow and sneak attack (HP 18 -> 10)."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "scout_kira",
        "changes": "Reduces arrow count by 1."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 1, Eirik's turn. Eirik will use his Action to attack Corrupted Wolf_2 with his mace and as a Bonus Action will cast Healing Word (level 1) on Scout Kira. For the attack: player must roll d20 +4 to hit (mace, melee, vs AC 13), and if hits, roll 1d6+2 for bludgeoning damage. For Healing Word: no attack roll needed, roll 1d4+3 (Wisdom modifier + Disciple of Life for extra healing). Await both rolls from player before resolving damage and healing. After Eirik's turn, Corrupted Wolf_3 will act to finish round 1.",
  "narration": "You tighten your grip on your mace, stepping in front of the wounded wolf as Kira staggers back, barely clinging to consciousness. With a prayer to your patron, you swing your weapon at the corrupted beast, hoping to finish it before it can strike again.\n\nAt the same time, you raise your holy symbol and call out a healing word, your voice ringing with divine command even above the chaos of snarls and snapping jaws. A warm, golden light streaks toward Kira, infusing her battered form with hope and strength.\n\nFirst, roll a d20 and add your +4 attack bonus to see if your mace lands true against Corrupted Wolf_2 (AC 13). Then, roll 1d6+2 for damage if you hit. For Healing Word, roll 1d4 and add +3 for your Wisdom and Disciple of Life bonus to restore Kira's HP. The wolves are closing, but this could turn the tide.",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 1, Eirik's turn concludes. Player scored a critical hit (natural 20) with the mace on Corrupted Wolf_2, rolling 2+6=8 on damage dice, plus 2 for modifier, for a total of 10 bludgeoning damage. Corrupted Wolf_2 had 10 HP and is now reduced to 0 HP—killed instantly by the blow. For bonus action, Eirik casts Healing Word on Kira, restoring 7 HP (4 rolled + 3 bonus from Wisdom/Disciple of Life). Kira returns to 10/10 HP, fully healed for now. Next and last to act this round is Corrupted Wolf_3 (initiative 1). After its actions, combat round will advance.",
  "narration": "Your battle cry drowns out the snarls as you bring your mace down with divine fury. The weapon arcs with unstoppable force, catching the corrupted wolf square on the skull. There's a sickening crunch and a spray of black ichor—the creature's eyes go dull and it collapses, motionless, before it can snap at Kira again.\n\nAlmost simultaneously, your healing word glows from your lips. Radiant warmth knits Kira's wounds closed, her breath coming easier as the pain lifts from her face. 'You're a miracle worker, Eirik!' she gasps, instantly looking steadier and ready for the fight.\n\nBut no time to celebrate—the last wolf, untouched and hungry, lunges from the shadows, its corrupted hide rippling with unnatural power. The battle is not yet done.",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "TW01-E2",
        "changes": "Corrupted Wolf_2 takes 10 bludgeoning damage from Eirik's critical mace strike and is killed instantly (HP 10 -> 0, status: dead)."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "scout_kira",
        "changes": "Restores 7 hit points from Eirik's Healing Word, returning to full health (10/10 HP)."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "Expends one 1st-level spell slot for Healing Word."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 1 concludes. Corrupted Wolf_3's turn: it targets Eirik, who had 7 HP. Wolf_3 hits twice—Bite (8 piercing), Corrupting Bite (5 necrotic)—for a total of 13 damage. Eirik's HP drops from 7 to -6. Immediately set Eirik's HP to 0, status to unconscious, and narrate him collapsing. Mark that Eirik cannot act in subsequent rounds unless stabilized. Combat_round advances to 2 as all creatures have acted. Next up: Corrupted Wolf (initiative 10) for round 2.",
  "narration": "Your furious shout and defiant stance make you the focal point of the wolves' rage. The last corrupted wolf launches at you, fangs bared, and clamps down with crushing force. Pain erupts in your arm as its teeth punch through armor and flesh alike. Before you can wrench free, it lunges again—its jaws suffused with unnatural corruption—and sinks them deep into your shoulder. \n\nThe world spins as agony and cold radiate from the wounds. Your vision tunnels, the cries of Kira and the snarl of the wolf muffled and distant. You stagger, then collapse to your knees, blood soaking the churned earth, as darkness closes in. Your shield arm slackens and you crumple, the world receding to a dull hum. \n\nKira's shout pierces the haze: 'Eirik! No!' The surviving wolves circle, eager for more blood, but the elf steps protectively over your fallen form, eyes fierce and desperate. You are down, unconscious, and teetering on the edge between life and death.",
  "combat_round": 2,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "Takes 13 total damage from Corrupted Wolf_3's bite and corrupting bite, HP reduced from 7 to 0, status set to unconscious. Eirik is now dying and cannot act until stabilized."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Audit and correction of Corrupted Wolf_3's attack on Eirik, end of round 1. Both attacks (Attack[19]=23 and Attack[13]=17) hit Eirik's AC 16. We now roll damage using the appropriate generic dice for each attack: Bite (2d4+2) using d4 [4,2], so 4+2+2=8 piercing; Corrupting Bite (1d6+2) using d6 [3], so 3+2=5 necrotic. Total damage is 8+5=13, matching the previously described 13. Eirik's HP goes from 7 to 0, status unconscious. No further change needed, but narration and action log should show dice and math for transparency. Proceed to round 2, Corrupted Wolf acts next.",
  "narration": "Let's clarify exactly what happened during the wolf's onslaught:\n\nAs you drew the beast's attention with a defiant shout, Corrupted Wolf_3 lunged. Its powerful jaws snapped shut on your arm with shattering force (attack roll 23 vs AC 16), dealing 8 piercing damage as the teeth punched through scale and flesh (damage: 2d4 [4,2] +2 = 8). Before you could wrench free, the wolf twisted and bit down a second time (attack roll 17 vs AC 16), and foul, necrotic energy surged into your veins (damage: 1d6 [3] +2 = 5 necrotic). \n\nThe total assault brought 13 damage in a matter of seconds (8 piercing, 5 necrotic). Since you had only 7 hit points remaining, the pain overwhelmed you and you collapsed, your vision swimming into blackness, your body landing hard on the churned, bloody earth. Kira's panicked voice is the last thing you hear as you slip from consciousness.\n\nYou are at 0 hit points, unconscious and dying. If you have questions about the rolls, you can see the breakdown above. The battle rages on without your immediate aid.",
  "combat_round": 2,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "Took 8 piercing damage (2d4 [4,2]+2) and 5 necrotic damage (1d6 [3]+2) from Corrupted Wolf_3. Total of 13 damage. HP reduced from 7 to 0, status set to unconscious."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Rules clarification mid-round. Eirik is unconscious at 0 HP and cannot act, including casting Spare the Dying or any action requiring movement or speech. Stabilization (such as Spare the Dying) must be performed by another creature, such as Kira, or Eirik must make death saving throws on his turns. Currently, Corrupted Wolf (initiative 10) is next to act, followed by Kira, before Eirik's own (inert) turn. DO NOT prompt Eirik for action—he is incapacitated and cannot stabilize himself.",
  "narration": "You drift in and out of darkness, the scent of blood and earth thick in your nostrils. Your limbs refuse to respond, and your thoughts are a swirl of memory and pain. In this state, you cannot speak, move, or call upon your faith—your hands slacken and will alone is not enough.\n\nTo receive the mercy of the gods, another must reach you—Kira, perhaps, or some other ally—or else fate itself will decide your survival. Spare the Dying and other means of stabilization must come from outside aid, not from your own will, while you are unconscious. Until then, all you can do is linger on the threshold, waiting for rescue or release.",
  "combat_round": 2,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 2 begins. Initiative order: Corrupted Wolf (10), Scout Kira (10), Eirik Hearthwise (6, unconscious—will need to roll a death saving throw on his turn), Corrupted Wolf_3 (1). Corrupted Wolf acts first, targeting Kira (the last standing threat). First attack: Bite (CREATURE ATTACKS d20 [9]+4=13 vs AC 15, miss). Second attack: Corrupting Bite (CREATURE ATTACKS d20 [17]+4=21 vs AC 15, hit). Damage: 1d6+2 necrotic (GENERIC DICE d6 [3]+2=5 necrotic). Next is Scout Kira, who will fire her shortbow at Corrupted Wolf_3 (most immediate threat, to split focus and gain Sneak Attack if possible). Attack roll: CREATURE ATTACKS d20 [8]+4=12 vs AC 13, miss. After Kira, Eirik will roll his first death saving throw. DO NOT prompt player yet, as these actions must resolve first.",
  "narration": "As the new round begins, the two wolves, fur bristling and eyes aflame with unnatural hunger, close in on Kira. The larger wolf snaps at her side but she twists away just in time. But its jaws come again, this time sinking deep into her hip with a burst of searing, necrotic agony. She grits her teeth, stifling a cry.\n\nRefusing to yield, Kira lets her instincts take over. She nocks another arrow and fires at the second wolf, but the shaft goes wide, ricocheting off a shattered wagon wheel. The beasts close in, black ichor dripping from their fangs.\n\nYou, Eirik, lie motionless in the mud—your fate poised on the edge of a blade as the chaos rages overhead.",
  "combat_round": 2,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "scout_kira",
        "changes": "Takes 5 necrotic damage from Corrupted Wolf's corrupting bite. Kira is now at 5 out of 10 HP."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "scout_kira",
        "changes": "Misses her shortbow attack against Corrupted Wolf_3."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 2, Eirik's death saving throw: 15 (success). Eirik now has 1 success, 0 failures. He remains unconscious but stable for now. Next in initiative is Corrupted Wolf_3 (1), who will attack the only standing threat—Scout Kira. First attack: Bite (CREATURE ATTACKS d20 [10]+4=14 vs AC 15, miss). Second attack: Corrupting Bite (CREATURE ATTACKS d20 [9]+4=13 vs AC 15, miss). Both attacks miss. Round 2 is now complete—all living creatures have acted. Advance to round 3, starting with Corrupted Wolf (initiative 10).",
  "narration": "Somewhere in the darkness, a flicker of strength returns—your will to live forces a ragged breath into your lungs. The battle rages overhead, but you hold on, refusing to slip further into the abyss. Your fate is not yet sealed.\n\nMeanwhile, the second corrupted wolf, jaws snapping hungrily, turns its focus fully on Kira. It lunges twice, teeth flashing and black rot flying, but she ducks and spins away, narrowly evading each deadly bite. The beast snarls in frustration, and Kira meets its gaze with a look of fierce defiance.\n\nThe clearing is slick with blood and shadow, and the odds are grim—but hope has not yet died. The fight presses into its next brutal exchange.",
  "combat_round": 3,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 3 in progress. Initiative order: Corrupted Wolf (10), Scout Kira (10), Eirik Hearthwise (6, unconscious—death saving throw up next), then Corrupted Wolf_3 (1). Corrupted Wolf's turn: two attacks on Kira, both miss. Scout Kira's turn: shortbow attack on Corrupted Wolf, hits for 9 piercing (no Sneak Attack since Eirik is unconscious). HP updated accordingly. It is now Eirik's turn for a death saving throw. STOP and prompt player to roll a d20. Do not process Corrupted Wolf_3 turn yet.",
  "narration": "The largest corrupted wolf lunges at Kira with wild ferocity, but she dances nimbly aside, battered but unbroken. Both sets of jaws snap shut on empty air—a breath from tearing her to the ground. Heart pounding, Kira draws and looses her arrow in a single motion. Her aim is true: the shaft buries itself deep in the wolf’s chest, and dark ichor pours from the wound. The creature staggers but remains on its feet, hate burning in its eyes as it turns its fury back on your companion.\n\nThe sounds of battle echo in your fading senses, Eirik. You are surrounded by darkness, but the distant cries and clash of survival pull at your spirit.\n\nEirik, it is your turn—clinging to life. Roll a d20 for your next death saving throw.",
  "combat_round": 3,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "TW01-E2",
        "changes": "Corrupted Wolf takes 9 piercing damage from Kira's shortbow (HP 18 -> 9)."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "scout_kira",
        "changes": "Spends one arrow firing at the Corrupted Wolf."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 3, Eirik's death saving throw: natural 20. This means Eirik regains 1 HP, immediately becomes conscious, and can act on his next turn. He is prone but aware. After this, Corrupted Wolf_3 (initiative 1) acts, targeting Kira with both attacks. Bite (CREATURE ATTACKS d20 [18]+4=22 vs AC 15, hit); damage 2d4+2 (GENERIC DICE d4 [3,4]+2 = 9 piercing). Corrupting Bite (CREATURE ATTACKS d20 [2]+4=6 vs AC 15, miss). Kira takes 9 piercing damage, dropping her from 5 HP to 0 HP—she is knocked unconscious. Round 3 is now complete; combat_round advances to 4, Corrupted Wolf acts first in the new round.",
  "narration": "A miracle in the mud: breath shudders back into your lungs and your eyes snap open, the world resolving in a haze of blood, rain, and the snarl of wolves. You are alive—barely—heart pounding and vision blurry, but you grip your mace with renewed desperation.\n\nAt that very moment, the second wolf barrels into Kira with unstoppable force. Its massive jaws clamp down on her shoulder and wrench her to the ground. The world slows as you see your friend's eyes widen in agony, then flutter closed as she slumps, limp and silent, into the soaked earth. The beast's second lunge misses, but the damage is done.\n\nYou are conscious with 1 HP, lying prone among splintered arrows and muddy grass. Kira is down, her fate uncertain. All around, the wolves circle, blood-slicked and relentless. The battle is far from over, but hope blazes anew within you.",
  "combat_round": 4,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "Rolls a natural 20 on death saving throw and immediately regains 1 hit point. Eirik is now conscious and prone."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "scout_kira",
        "changes": "Takes 9 piercing damage from Corrupted Wolf_3's bite, dropping from 5 to 0 HP and falling unconscious."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 4, Eirik's turn (player acting after Kira's death save, which will be resolved next). Player targets the wounded Corrupted Wolf (HP 9/18) with the flask of alchemist's fire. Attack at disadvantage: 14 (lower roll) +1 (Dex modifier) = 15, which beats the wolf's AC 13. The flask hits! Now resolve fire damage: player must roll 1d4 for initial fire damage (not yet rolled). The wolf will take 1d4 fire at the start of its turns until extinguished. After the throw, Eirik casts Cure Wounds on himself (1d8+3, also awaiting roll from player). Next, Scout Kira must make a death saving throw (await roll from player). After resolving these rolls, Corrupted Wolf_3 will act to complete the round.",
  "narration": "Summoning the last of your battered strength, you hurl the flask of alchemist's fire at the snarling wolf already wounded by Kira's arrow. The glass arcs through the smoky air and shatters against the beast's hide, splattering it with burning liquid. Flames burst to life along its matted fur, and the wolf recoils, yelping—a wild, pained sound unlike anything you've heard from its corrupted throat. The fire clings, promising agony to come.\n\nGasping, you press your bloodied hand to your chest and whisper a desperate prayer. Radiance gathers beneath your skin—renewal, hope, life. The pain in your wounds begins to ebb, and warmth floods your limbs even as smoke and fire swirl around you.\n\nBefore the wolves can recover, and as fire spreads, your fate—and Kira's—hangs in the balance. Roll 1d4 for the initial fire damage to the wolf, and 1d8+3 for the healing you receive. Then, Kira will need to make a death saving throw as the battle blazes on.",
  "combat_round": 4,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 4, Eirik's turn resolution. The flask of alchemist's fire hits the wounded Corrupted Wolf, dealing 2 fire damage (HP 9 -> 7). At the start of each of its turns, it will take 1d4 fire damage unless it spends its action to extinguish the flames. Eirik then casts Cure Wounds on himself, healing 7 HP (1 + 7 = 8 HP total, removing the risk of immediately falling again). Next, Scout Kira must make a death saving throw (await player roll). After that, Corrupted Wolf_3 will act, targeting Eirik since Kira is down. Round remains 4 until all creatures have acted.",
  "narration": "The flask bursts in a rush of flame, splattering the already-wounded wolf with liquid fire. The beast yelps and bucks wildly, its fur igniting in flickering orange and blue—the scent of burning rot fills the clearing. The flames cling, promising further pain if the wolf cannot shake them free.\n\nYou draw in a ragged breath and press your hand to your wounds, chanting the sacred words of healing. Golden light surges through your battered body, closing torn flesh and lending strength to trembling limbs. You feel a surge of hope, battered but unbroken, as life and warmth return to your veins.\n\nKira lies pale and unmoving, her fate hanging by a thread as the battle rages. The surviving corrupted wolf circles, its eyes fixed hungrily on you—the last defender standing. The flames, your resolve, and the gods themselves are all that separate you from oblivion.\n\nRoll a d20 for Scout Kira's death saving throw.",
  "combat_round": 4,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "TW01-E2",
        "changes": "Corrupted Wolf takes 2 fire damage from alchemist's fire (HP 9 -> 7) and is now burning, will take 1d4 fire damage at the start of its future turns unless extinguished."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "Heals 7 hit points from Cure Wounds. Eirik is now at 8 out of 11 HP. Expends one 1st-level spell slot. No longer at immediate risk of unconsciousness."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 4, Scout Kira's turn. Death saving throw result: 19 (success). Kira now has 1 success, 0 failures, and remains unconscious but stable for now. Last in initiative is Corrupted Wolf_3 (1), which will target Eirik, the only conscious foe. Attack 1: Bite (CREATURE ATTACKS d20 [5]+4=9 vs AC 16, miss). Attack 2: Corrupting Bite (CREATURE ATTACKS d20 [9]+4=13 vs AC 16, miss). Both attacks miss. With all living creatures now having acted, advance to combat_round 5. Corrupted Wolf (initiative 10) will act first and will take 1d4 fire damage at the start of its turn before it can act.",
  "narration": "A ragged breath escapes Kira's lips as the light flickers behind her closed eyes—her spirit refuses to yield, and she clings to life, though the wolves still prowl so close.\n\nYou, battered but alive, square off against the remaining beasts. The third wolf lunges, but you parry one snapping bite with your shield and roll aside from the second. The world narrows to the crackle of fire, the stench of burning fur, and the rasp of your own breath in your ears.\n\nYou and the wolves are bloodied and desperate, but for a heartbeat, hope lingers. The next moments will decide everything. The burning wolf's pain is only beginning as the fire eats at its side, and Kira's fate hangs by a thread.",
  "combat_round": 5,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "scout_kira",
        "changes": "Rolls a 19 on her death saving throw and has 1 success, 0 failures. Remains unconscious and stable for now."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 5, start of initiative. 1) The burning Corrupted Wolf takes 1d4 fire damage at the start of its turn before it acts—player rolled 2 last round, now roll next from GENERIC DICE d4 [1] = 1 fire damage. Wolf HP drops from 7 to 6. 2) Eirik can use Spare the Dying on Kira, but it requires an ACTION (not a bonus or free action). Eirik must move adjacent to Kira (if not already), then use his action to stabilize her—no roll required. This will prevent further death saves if successful. 3) Corrupted Wolf (initiative 10) will then take its two attacks on Eirik. After, Kira's turn (if conscious), then Eirik's, then Corrupted Wolf_3. Player turn is not yet active. DO NOT prompt for player action yet.",
  "narration": "As the new round begins, the wolf still wreathed in alchemical fire howls in agony as fresh flames bite deeper into its corrupted flesh. Burning and wounded, it hesitates for a moment, but the pain only stokes its fury.\n\nYou spot Kira lying deathly still on the earth—her life hanging in the balance. Though your instinct is to rush to her aid with your cleric's touch, you recall that the power of Spare the Dying demands both your focus and a precious few seconds. You must move to her side and use your action to invoke the spell. It is not a mere gesture or word but a deliberate act of mercy.\n\nThe wolves, meanwhile, are not yet done with you. The burning beast snarls and charges, fire trailing from its matted fur. The next moments will test every ounce of your resolve.",
  "combat_round": 5,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "TW01-E2",
        "changes": "Corrupted Wolf takes 1 fire damage at the start of its turn from alchemist's fire (HP 7 -> 6)."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 5, Corrupted Wolf (initiative 10) acts now. Wolf takes 1 fire damage at start of turn (previously resolved, HP 7 -> 6). It then uses its two attacks on Eirik, the only conscious foe: Bite (CREATURE ATTACKS d20 [13]+4=17 vs AC 16, HIT), damage 2d4+2 (GENERIC DICE d4 [4,1]+2=7 piercing). Corrupting Bite (CREATURE ATTACKS d20 [1]+4=5 vs AC 16, MISS). After this, it will be Scout Kira's turn for a death saving throw, then Eirik's turn, then Corrupted Wolf_3. DO NOT prompt player for action yet—resolve wolf's attacks first.",
